OL,3,CSurgeon who had legs amputated accused
OL,4,Cof falsely claiming he had sepsis
OL,6,FA vascular surgeon from Truro who
OL,7,Fcarried out hundreds of amputation
OL,8,Foperations before having his own legs
OL,9,Fremoved has been charged with fraud.
OL,11,FNeil Hopper, 49, who worked for the
OL,12,FRoyal Cornwall Hospitals Trust for 10
OL,13,Fyears until 2023, claimed his leg
OL,14,Finjuries were the result of sepsis.
OL,16,FHe has also been charged with
OL,17,Fencouraging someone else to remove the
OL,18,Fbody parts of others.
